The Dirt Circle Dogs are an indie-rock band from Denver, CO. Dan, Aaron, Sondra and Eric are all multi-instrumentalists and artists with interests ranging from illustration and design to experimental theatre, and punk-rock to choral music. The resulting aesthetic combines rigid structure and tradition with curiosity, exploration, chaos and a love for finding the glimmer of darkness in all the sunshine. 

The bright dark sounds of DCD have been compared to Low, Papa M, Radiohead, Modest Mouse and Portishead, with a constantly-shifting instrumentation that ranges from a standard rock lineup to include cello, violin, mandolin, glockenspiel, sampling and more.

The southside of Chicago has long been a hotbed for the up‚Äêand‚Äêcoming talent and the newest trends in dance music. Setting the pace for the current Chicago sound is its newest favorite sons ‚Äê Ghetto Division ‚Äê who are making their ‚Äúown lane in the club music game.‚Äù Native‚Äêborn Chicagoian Eddie Regalado Jr, AKA DJ Rampage is one of the crew‚Äôs most renowned producers. From humble beginnings as a mobile DJ, he‚Äôs become a seasoned veteran of Chicago‚Äôs club and party scene, taking the decks in the mid‚Äê90‚Äôs to craft a unique style inspired by the city‚Äôs own house music. Since then he‚Äôs collected influences as easily as praise, combining a love for juke, techno, disco as well as the odd bit of funk, film soundtracks and video game sound effects. A Rampage production is likely to be energetic, house‚Äêinfluenced, and unpredictable, yet above all, quintessentially Chicagoian. In an effort to promote this forward‚Äêthinking style, Rampage along with @CharlieGlitch, @Maddjazz and @RobThreezy formed the DJ/production crew known as @GhettoDivision, and together have exposed their characteristic sound to the dance music scene. And the scene is listening. Besides a highly‚Äêpublicized alliance with the New Jersey / Philadelphia based @BrickBandits, Rampage has shared the decks with celebrated and infamous trendsetters by the likes of @Diplo, @DJSega, @ToySelectah, @Flosstradamus, and made clubs bang across California and the Midwest, as well as SXSW, Canada, Mexico & Europe.

For this reason he is fervently opposed to manufactured pop music and it‚Äôs urban counter part R&B which has sold it‚Äôs soul to the Devil and is so busy gulping down his black scaly pecker it doesn‚Äôt realise that it has neither Rhythm nor Blues anymore. He is however, quite willing to listen to anything and for this reason believes that mashups (bootlegs/bastard pop) may save the world by extricating the faecal matter from pop music and making even the most banal and insipid music eminently listenable.  For this reason mashups will form part of the constitution for the GingerZilla's New World Order (which also includes a stipulation that record company executives are made to bathe in their own pop filth). 

The path of a fanatic towards world conquest is never easy and doesn't happen overnight (just mainy on Tuesday's), taking careful planning and bouts of extreme violence that must be done in the face of the evil that is Bill Gates and his unstable software (seriously did Ghenghis Khan have to put up with this?).

GingerZilla began making computer based tracks back in 2003/4 having tried (and failed) to make anything worth listening to on a antiquated keyboard that refused to connect to anything. After a promising start a serious virus put paid to his plans of world conquest and he was just able to save his efforts before making off from the smoking remnants before the whole thing blew up. What follows are those relics, the words and sounds of a new order...

Music and art can very much touch us with the essence of symmetry, balance, fluidity, cohesion whilst their counterparts: dis-juncture, chaos, inertia, provide the tension that makes for the through-line: Story.

No wonder then that Xavier Morel, a veteran and simply awesome producer and Dj speaks in such terms. In these days where the distinction between artist and playlist are becoming less distinct, the essence of audio art is becoming distilled in its import.

"The most important concept in music is not the way you play your tracks but the story you make with them! Mixing and music is my passion and my career. I hope to carry and share this as long as possible!" - Xavier Morel

Starting his DJ career off in 1988 Xavier has Dj'd throughout Europe, Australia and Asia, most particularly Japan where he was based for years.

On the production front has worked and collaborated with Juno Reactor, Prime Suspect, Section X, Eat Static, Fuel, Carcharodon Megalodon, VX & H229 (on Machine Label),Marcus Maichel,Shane Berry,Oz Morsley ,and project comming with greg hunter,Marcus Maichel, and an other with Athena Ekkynos Etana, on contruction .

  Stanley Chounard of Urbana Illinois USA, AKA Clayjrjr2 is a determined musician/composer/producer/artist who started out his music making career by using a very simple MIDI sequencer. He became interested in making his own tunes because he had nothing new to breakdance to.
  After a short while someone introduced him to a way more advanced audio software program called Fruityloops. Harmonious Discord Recordings has been the purveyor of offbeat melodies for DJ‚Äôs and producers ‚Äúin-the-know‚Äù for over 20 years. Founded in 2001 by Moon Magnet productions front men Sean Anderson, Brad Denton, and David Brown; HD‚Äôs aim has been to provide a musical outlet for artists that continue to defy convention at every opportunity. Harmonious Discord‚Äôs name was devised to represent a collective rebellion against the sea of mediocre and brainless music polluting the airwaves. Its motto ‚ÄúCacophony at its Finest‚Äù displays the contrast of what some view as noise (or cacophony) and what others view as music. The beauty of music is that it is subjective and the brilliance lies with the listener. We have strived in our 10 year run to combine the innovative and legendary sounds of Jazz and the new and basic sounds of the tech revolution, which is represented in our logo (a martini glass w/ sprocket).

Originally a vinyl only media Harmonious Discord released its first vinyl record in January of 2002 with a premier release by two of Harmonious Discords home-based artists; Ahman (David Brown) and newly added artist Litex (Eric Reeves). The project received warm regards but did not make a huge splash in the electronic music community. It wasn‚Äôt till their second release, a techy offbeat two tracker by Austin native Merrick Brown, that HD was written into the books of dance music history. The second release was canned by DJ notables from all over the world and quickly rose to the top of the balance chart. In 2003 we saw another huge hit with the release of Grey‚Äôs first HD release titled ‚ÄúNaughty Glances‚Äù and the floor filling remix by Seattle‚Äôs own Jacob London. The vinyl only production continued until 2007 when Harmonious Discord decided to embrace the digital revolution and joined forces with Beatport, the industries leader in digital distribution. Many years later our family has grown to encompass artists like Chakaharta and Patchen Preston who have forged a solid foundation using Harmonious Discord as their main production outlet. Harmonious Discord has forged onward with digital releases that span multiple genre‚Äôs and showcase some of the most forward thinking artists in today‚Äôs electronic music landscape.
